  "analytics_identifier": null,
  "base_path": "/correct-employee-overpaid-ni",
  "content_id": "2e55e671-15f0-4eec-af15-b93f2e5b6f2f",
  "description": "Fix a National Insurance contribution payment if you paid an employee the wrong amount after 6 November 2022.",
  "details": {
    "body": "<p>National Insurance rates changed on 6 November 2022. As a result, you might need to make a correction to National Insurance contributions.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>This tool is also available <a href=\"/cywiro-cyg-a-ordalwyd-gan-gyflogai\">in Welsh (Cymraeg)</a>.</p>\n</div>\n\n<p>You can use this tool if you’re an employer and both of the following are true:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>you paid your employee on or after 6 November 2022</li>\n  <li>your payroll software had not updated to use the new <a href=\"/national-insurance-rates-letters\">National Insurance rate</a> when you made the payment</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Find out <a href=\"/payroll-errors\">how to fix another type of payroll problem</a>.</p>\n</div>\n",
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "nodes": [
      {
        "body": "<p>You can usually amend an incorrect National Insurance contribution payment calculation in your next regular Full Payment Submission (FPS).</p>\n\n<p>In some cases, you might not be able to send a revised FPS. For example, if you’ve gone bankrupt or if the employee has left and you do not have their details.</p>\n",
        "kind": "question",
        "options": [
          {
            "label": "Yes, I can submit a revised FPS",
            "next_node": "question-2",
            "slug": "yes-i-can-submit-a-revised-fps"
          },
          {
            "label": "No, I cannot submit a revised FPS",
            "next_node": "question-3",
            "slug": "no-i-cannot-submit-a-revised-fps"
          }
        ],
        "slug": "question-1",
        "title": "Can you submit a revised Full Payment Submission?"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>After you’ve submitted a revised Full Payment Submission (FPS), you need to refund your employee any National Insurance contributions they overpaid.</p>\n\n<p>In some cases, you might not be able to refund an employee. For example, if they no longer work for you.</p>\n",
        "kind": "question",
        "options": [
          {
            "label": "Yes, I can refund my employee",
            "next_node": "outcome-1",
            "slug": "yes-i-can-refund-my-employee"
          },
          {
            "label": "No, I cannot refund my employee",
            "next_node": "outcome-2",
            "slug": "no-i-cannot-refund-my-employee"
          }
        ],
        "slug": "question-2",
        "title": "Can you refund any overpayments?"
      },
      {
        "kind": "question",
        "options": [
          {
            "label": "30 or more employees",
            "next_node": "outcome-3",
            "slug": "30-or-more-employees"
          },
          {
            "label": "Fewer than 30 employees",
            "next_node": "outcome-4",
            "slug": "fewer-than-30-employees"
          }
        ],
        "slug": "question-3",
        "title": "How many employees are you making a correction for?"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>To fix incorrect payments you should:</p>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li>\n<p>Work out the correct National Insurance contributions for any payments made between 6 November and the date when your software was updated.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Either report the correct figures on your next <a href=\"/running-payroll/reporting-to-hmrc\">Full Payment Submission (FPS)</a> or send an additional FPS before your next regular FPS is due. Do not resubmit individual payments.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Refund any overpayments of National Insurance contributions to your employee with their next pay.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"sending-an-additional-fps\">Sending an additional FPS</h2>\n\n<p>To do this, you need to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>update the ‘this pay period’ figures with the difference between what you originally reported and the correct figures</li>\n  <li>correct the year-to-date figures</li>\n  <li>use the same payment date as the original FPS</li>\n  <li>put the same pay frequency as the original FPS</li>\n  <li>put ‘H - Correction to earlier submission’ in the ‘Late reporting reason’ field</li>\n</ul>\n",
        "kind": "outcome",
        "options": [

        ],
        "slug": "outcome-1",
        "title": "Submit an FPS and refund overpayments"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>To fix incorrect payments you should:</p>\n\n<ol class=\"steps\">\n<li>\n<p>Work out the correct National Insurance contributions for any payments made between 6 November and the date when your software was updated.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Either report the correct figures on your next <a href=\"/running-payroll/reporting-to-hmrc\">Full Payment Submission (FPS)</a> or send an additional FPS before your next regular FPS is due. Do not resubmit individual payments.</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n\n<h2 id=\"sending-an-additional-fps\">Sending an additional FPS</h2>\n\n<p>To do this, you need to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>update the ‘this pay period’ figures with the difference between what you originally reported and the correct figures</li>\n  <li>correct the year-to-date figures</li>\n  <li>use the same payment date as the original FPS</li>\n  <li>put the same pay frequency as the original FPS</li>\n  <li>put ‘H - Correction to earlier submission’ in the ‘Late reporting reason’ field</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"refund-the-overpayment-to-your-employee\">Refund the overpayment to your employee</h2>\n\n<p>You’ll need to write to HMRC.</p>\n\n<p>In the letter, include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the reference ‘NILEVY061122’</li>\n  <li>the name, date of birth and National Insurance number for each employee</li>\n  <li>that your application is for a refund of National Insurance contributions due to the National Insurance rate change</li>\n  <li>why you cannot submit a revised Full Payment Submission (FPS)</li>\n  <li>which tax years you overpaid in</li>\n  <li>how much National Insurance you overpaid</li>\n  <li>why you cannot make the payment to the employee</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>For a claim for one employee, send the letter to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nHM Revenue and Customs   \n<br>National Insurance Contributions and Employer Office   \n<br>BX9 1AN  \n<br>\n</p></div></div>\n\n<p>For a claim for 2 or more employees, send the letter to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n  \nHM Revenue and Customs   \n<br>National Insurance Contributions and Employer Office   \n<br>BX9 1BX  \n<br>\n</p></div></div>\n",
        "kind": "outcome",
        "options": [

        ],
        "slug": "outcome-2",
        "title": "Submit an FPS and write to HMRC"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You need to write to HMRC.</p>\n\n<p>In the letter, include:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the reference ‘NILEVY061122’</li>\n  <li>the name, date of birth and National Insurance number for each employee</li>\n  <li>that your application is for a refund of National Insurance contributions due to the National Insurance rate change</li>\n  <li>why you cannot submit a revised Full Payment Submission (FPS)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Send the letter to:</p>\n\n<div class=\"address\"><div class=\"adr org fn\"><p>\n\nHM Revenue and Customs   \n<br>National Insurance Contributions and Employer Office   \n<br>BX9 1BX\n<br>\n</p></div></div>\n",
        "kind": "outcome",
        "options": [

        ],
        "slug": "outcome-3",
        "title": "Make a correction for 30 or more employees"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You can submit a correction form. You’ll need a Government Gateway ID.</p>\n\n<p><a class=\"gem-c-button govuk-button govuk-button--start\" role=\"button\" data-module=\"govuk-button\" draggable=\"false\" href=\"https://www.tax.service.gov.uk/submissions/new-form/ask-hmrc-to-check-if-you-have-declared-too-much-national-insurance-contributions-in-2022-2023\"><span> Start now </span><svg class=\"govuk-button__start-icon govuk-!-display-none-print\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"17.5\" height=\"19\" viewbox=\"0 0 33 40\" focusable=\"false\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path fill=\"currentColor\" d=\"M0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z\"></path></svg></a></p>\n\n<h2 id=\"after-you-submit-your-application\">After you submit your application</h2>\n\n<p>HMRC will write to you and tell you what to do next.</p>\n",
        "kind": "outcome",
        "options": [

        ],
        "slug": "outcome-4",
        "title": "Make a correction for fewer than 30 employees"
      }
    ],
    "start_button_text": "Start now"
  },
